In C, the **Greater Than (>)** and **Less Than (` (Greater Than)** checks if the left value is **larger** than the right value.
* **`

int main() {
    int score = 75;

    // Greater Than: Check if score is greater than 50
    if (score > 50) {
        printf("Pass\n");
    }

    int age = 16;

    // Less Than: Check if age is less than 18
    if (age < 18) {
        printf("Minor\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
```

**Expected Output:**

```default
Pass
Minor
```

